  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>You will lead cost analysis and estimation for carpentry and related trades within interior fit-out projects, managing contracts and budgets to drive project success. You will prepare tender and contract documents, manage subcontractor relations, and resolve contractual claims to ensure timely, cost-effective delivery.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Analyze and estimate costs for carpentry works and other trades within interior fit-out projects to support accurate budgeting and contract administration</li><li>Monitor project budgets and track expenditures to ensure financial control and alignment with project goals</li><li>Prepare tender and contract documents, including bills of quantities, by performing quantity take-offs, sourcing materials, and estimating costs to facilitate competitive tendering</li><li>Draft letters of award to subcontractors and verify claims to maintain cost control and contractual compliance</li><li>Identify and prepare variation orders for projects to address scope changes and maintain project profitability</li><li>Obtain and evaluate subcontractor and supplier quotations to support cost-effective procurement decisions</li><li>Source new vendors and conduct cost comparisons to optimize supplier selection and project costs</li><li>Ensure contract quantities and variation orders are accurately updated for awarded projects and perform cost-benefit analyses to inform decision-making</li><li>Manage the resolution of contractual claims across all project stages, from pre-tender to post-contract, to mitigate risks and protect company interests</li><li>Attend site surveys as required to assess project conditions and support accurate cost estimations</li><li>Perform additional duties as assigned to support project and organizational objectives</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge and passion for interior fit-out and builders work in retail and commercial environments, with 3 to 5 years of experience in carpentry or retail fit-out projects</li><li>Experience delivering projects with demonstrated ability to manage challenges related to time, cost, and quality control, and to exceed expectations</li><li>Proficiency in MS Office applications including Excel, Word, and PowerPoint</li><li>Familiarity with MEP systems and Bluebeam software is advantageous</li><li>Understanding of the Gebiz tender process</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
